{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JsLUG3dKskmhgpEtSnyKFN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F27 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC.md §7.6 — Testing Page (`/test`), Left Panel:\n6\t\n7\t### Layout\n8\t- Two-panel layout: **Left panel — Event Sender** (controls to fire events), **Right panel — Live Feed** (real-time stream of incoming events)\n9\t\n10\t### Left Panel — Event Sender\n11\t\n12\t**Quick-fire buttons** (pre-configured payloads, one click to send):\n13\t\n14\t| Button | Event Name | Payload |\n15\t|---|---|---|\n16\t| Anonymous Page View | `Page Viewed` | random device_id, `{ page: \"/home\" }` |\n17\t| Button Click | `Button Clicked` | same device_id as last anonymous, `{ button_name: \"Get Started\" }` |\n18\t| Identify User | _(identity link)_ | same device_id + `user_id: \"test@example.com\"` |\n19\t| Purchase | `Purchase Completed` | `user_id: \"test@example.com\"`, `{ amount: 49.99, currency: \"USD\" }` |\n20\t| Signup | `Signup Completed` | new random device_id, new random user_id |\n21\t| Custom Event | _(form)_ | manual fields |\n22\t\n23\t**Custom Event Form** (collapsible):\n24\t- `event_name` text input\n25\t- `device_id` text input (optional)\n26\t- `user_id` text input (optional)\n27\t- `timestamp` datetime input (optional)\n28\t- `properties` JSON textarea with syntax highlighting (CodeMirror or simple `<textarea>`)\n29\t- Submit button\n30\t\n31\tAfter each send, show inline success/error toast under the button.\n32\t\n33\t**Seed Data button**: calls `POST /api/seed` with a loading indicator. Shows event count after completion.\n34\t\n35\t## Dependencies\n36\t\n37\tCompleted features this builds on:\n38\t- F5 (`POST /api/events` route) — `src/app/api/events/route.ts`\n39\t- F4 (identity resolution) — `src/lib/identity.ts`\n40\t- F16 (seed route) — `src/app/api/seed/route.ts`, `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts`\n41\t- F17 (live SSE route) — `src/app/api/live/route.ts` (will be used by the right panel, but this feature only builds the left panel)\n42\t- F18 (navigation shell) — `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `src/app/layout.tsx`\n43\t\n44\tExisting files that will be imported or extended:\n45\t- `src/app/test/page.tsx` (currently a stub — will be replaced)\n46\t- `POST /api/events` at `src/app/api/events/route.ts` (consumed, not modified)\n47\t- `POST /api/seed` at `src/app/api/seed/route.ts` (consumed, not modified)\n48\t- `GET /api/seed/status` at `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts` (consumed, not modified)\n49\t\n50\t## Files to create or modify\n51\t\n52\t- CREATE `src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx` — Quick-fire button grid with pre-configured payloads\n53\t- CREATE `src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx` — Collapsible custom event form\n54\t- CREATE `src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx` — Seed data trigger with loading state and event count display\n55\t- CREATE `src/components/test/useEventSender.ts` — Hook encapsulating event sending logic, device_id tracking, toast state\n56\t- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/useEventSender.test.ts` — Unit tests for the hook\n57\t- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/QuickFireButtons.test.tsx` — Component tests for quick-fire buttons\n58\t- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx` — Component tests for custom event form\n59\t- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/SeedDataButton.test.tsx` — Component tests for seed data button\n60\t- MODIFY `src/app/test/page.tsx` — Replace stub with two-panel layout composing left panel components (right panel placeholder for future F28)\n61\t\n62\t## Implementation order\n63\t\n64\t1. **Create `src/components/test/useEventSender.ts`** — Custom hook that:\n65\t   - Tracks `lastDeviceId` in state (for Anonymous Page View → Button Click → Identify flow)\n66\t   - Exposes `sendEvent(payload)` that POSTs to `/api/events` and returns success/error\n67\t   - Exposes `sendSeed()` that POSTs to `/api/seed` then GETs `/api/seed/status`\n68\t   - Manages per-button toast/feedback state (success message, error message, loading)\n69\t   - Generates random device_id and user_id values for quick-fire buttons\n70\t\n71\t2. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/useEventSender.test.ts`** — Unit tests for the hook\n72\t\n73\t3. **Create `src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx`** — Renders the 5 quick-fire buttons (Anonymous Page View, Button Click, Identify User, Purchase, Signup). Each button calls `sendEvent` from the hook with the correct payload. Shows inline success/error feedback after each send.\n74\t\n75\t4. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/QuickFireButtons.test.tsx`** — Component tests\n76\t\n77\t5. **Create `src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx`** — Collapsible form with event_name, device_id, user_id, timestamp, and properties (textarea) fields. Submit button calls `sendEvent`. Shows inline success/error feedback.\n78\t\n79\t6. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx`** — Component tests\n80\t\n81\t7. **Create `src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx`** — Button that calls `POST /api/seed`, shows loading spinner, then displays event count from seed result or `/api/seed/status`.\n82\t\n83\t8. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/SeedDataButton.test.tsx`** — Component tests\n84\t\n85\t9. **Modify `src/app/test/page.tsx`** — Replace stub with two-panel layout. Left panel renders QuickFireButtons, CustomEventForm, and SeedDataButton. Right panel renders a placeholder (e.g., `<Typography>Live Feed coming soon</Typography>`) for the future live feed feature.\n86\t\n87\t## Sprint contract\n88\t\n89\t- [ ] Type check: `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n90\t- [ ] Lint: `pnpm lint` exits 0\n91\t- [ ] Build: `pnpm build` exits 0\n92\t- [ ] Test suite: `pnpm test` exits with 0 failures\n93\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/useEventSender.ts` exists and exports `useEventSender`\n94\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx` exists and exports `QuickFireButtons`\n95\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx` exists and exports `CustomEventForm`\n96\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx` exists and exports `SeedDataButton`\n97\t- [ ] File `src/app/test/page.tsx` exists and imports from `@/components/test/QuickFireButtons`\n98\t- [ ] File `src/app/test/page.tsx` imports from `@/components/test/CustomEventForm`\n99\t- [ ] File `src/app/test/page.tsx` imports from `@/components/test/SeedDataButton`\n100\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `data-testid=\"quick-fire-buttons\"`\n101\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `data-testid=\"custom-event-form\"`\n102\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `data-testid=\"seed-data-button\"`\n103\t\n104\t## Test plan\n105\t\n106\t- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/useEventSender.test.ts`\n107\t- **Module under test**: `useEventSender` hook from `@/components/test/useEventSender`\n108\t- **Cases to cover**:\n109\t  - `sendEvent` calls `fetch` with `POST /api/events` and correct JSON body\n110\t  - `sendEvent` returns success state on 201 response\n111\t  - `sendEvent` returns error message on 400/409/500 responses\n112\t  - `lastDeviceId` is updated after sending an Anonymous Page View event\n113\t  - `sendSeed` calls `POST /api/seed` and returns event count on success\n114\t  - `sendSeed` returns error message on failure\n115\t  - Loading state is true during in-flight requests, false after completion\n116\t\n117\t- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/QuickFireButtons.test.tsx`\n118\t- **Module under test**: `QuickFireButtons` component from `@/components/test/QuickFireButtons`\n119\t- **Cases to cover**:\n120\t  - Renders `data-testid=\"quick-fire-buttons\"` container\n121\t  - Renders all 5 quick-fire buttons (Anonymous Page View, Button Click, Identify User, Purchase, Signup)\n122\t  - Clicking \"Anonymous Page View\" calls `sendEvent` with `event_name: \"Page Viewed\"`, a device_id, and `{ page: \"/home\" }` properties\n123\t  - Clicking \"Button Click\" calls `sendEvent` with `event_name: \"Button Clicked\"` and same device_id as last anonymous event\n124\t  - Clicking \"Identify User\" calls `sendEvent` with both device_id and user_id\n125\t  - Clicking \"Purchase\" calls `sendEvent` with user_id and `{ amount: 49.99, currency: \"USD\" }`\n126\t  - Clicking \"Signup\" calls `sendEvent` with new random device_id and user_id\n127\t  - Success/error feedback is displayed after a send completes\n128\t\n129\t- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx`\n130\t- **Module under test**: `CustomEventForm` component from `@/components/test/CustomEventForm`\n131\t- **Cases to cover**:\n132\t  - Renders `data-testid=\"custom-event-form\"` container\n133\t  - Form is collapsible (toggle open/closed)\n134\t  - Submit button is disabled when `event_name` is empty\n135\t  - Submitting with valid event_name calls `sendEvent` with correct payload\n136\t  - Optional fields (device_id, user_id, timestamp, properties) are included in payload when filled\n137\t  - Invalid JSON in properties textarea shows validation error\n138\t  - Success/error feedback is displayed after submit\n139\t\n140\t- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/SeedDataButton.test.tsx`\n141\t- **Module under test**: `SeedDataButton` component from `@/components/test/SeedDataButton`\n142\t- **Cases to cover**:\n143\t  - Renders `data-testid=\"seed-data-button\"` container\n144\t  - Clicking the button calls `POST /api/seed`\n145\t  - Shows loading indicator while seed is in progress\n146\t  - Displays event count on successful completion\n147\t  - Shows error message on failure\n148\t\n149\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `/test` page rendering — requires dev server\n150\t\n151\t## Risks and open questions\n152\t\n153\t1. **device_id persistence across quick-fire buttons**: The spec says \"Button Click\" uses \"same device_id as last anonymous\" and \"Identify User\" uses \"same device_id\". The `useEventSender` hook must track the last generated device_id in React state. If the user refreshes the page, this tracking resets — acceptable since this is a developer testing tool.\n154\t2. **Properties textarea vs CodeMirror**: The spec mentions \"syntax highlighting (CodeMirror or simple `<textarea>`)\". Using a plain `<textarea>` with monospace font to avoid adding a CodeMirror dependency. The spec explicitly permits this.\n155\t3. **Right panel placeholder**: This feature only builds the left panel. The right panel (Live Feed) will be built in a subsequent feature. A placeholder is rendered to maintain the two-panel layout structure.\n156\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27b757f3-6d9d-4fd7-9868-cc1b8f1bb385","uuid":"b11a5eaf-a1de-4d7d-ba08-d47a1d6e4e30","timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:46:11.675Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F27-plan.md","content":"# F27 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC.md §7.6 — Testing Page (`/test`), Left Panel:\n\n### Layout\n- Two-panel layout: **Left panel — Event Sender** (controls to fire events), **Right panel — Live Feed** (real-time stream of incoming events)\n\n### Left Panel — Event Sender\n\n**Quick-fire buttons** (pre-configured payloads, one click to send):\n\n| Button | Event Name | Payload |\n|---|---|---|\n| Anonymous Page View | `Page Viewed` | random device_id, `{ page: \"/home\" }` |\n| Button Click | `Button Clicked` | same device_id as last anonymous, `{ button_name: \"Get Started\" }` |\n| Identify User | _(identity link)_ | same device_id + `user_id: \"test@example.com\"` |\n| Purchase | `Purchase Completed` | `user_id: \"test@example.com\"`, `{ amount: 49.99, currency: \"USD\" }` |\n| Signup | `Signup Completed` | new random device_id, new random user_id |\n| Custom Event | _(form)_ | manual fields |\n\n**Custom Event Form** (collapsible):\n- `event_name` text input\n- `device_id` text input (optional)\n- `user_id` text input (optional)\n- `timestamp` datetime input (optional)\n- `properties` JSON textarea with syntax highlighting (CodeMirror or simple `<textarea>`)\n- Submit button\n\nAfter each send, show inline success/error toast under the button.\n\n**Seed Data button**: calls `POST /api/seed` with a loading indicator. Shows event count after completion.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on:\n- F5 (`POST /api/events` route) — `src/app/api/events/route.ts`\n- F4 (identity resolution) — `src/lib/identity.ts`\n- F16 (seed route) — `src/app/api/seed/route.ts`, `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts`\n- F17 (live SSE route) — `src/app/api/live/route.ts` (will be used by the right panel, but this feature only builds the left panel)\n- F18 (navigation shell) — `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `src/app/layout.tsx`\n\nExisting files that will be imported or extended:\n- `src/app/test/page.tsx` (currently a stub — will be replaced)\n- `POST /api/events` at `src/app/api/events/route.ts` (consumed, not modified)\n- `POST /api/seed` at `src/app/api/seed/route.ts` (consumed, not modified)\n- `GET /api/seed/status` at `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts` (consumed, not modified)\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- CREATE `src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx` — Quick-fire button grid with pre-configured payloads\n- CREATE `src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx` — Collapsible custom event form\n- CREATE `src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx` — Seed data trigger with loading state and event count display\n- CREATE `src/components/test/useEventSender.ts` — Hook encapsulating event sending logic, device_id tracking, toast state\n- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/useEventSender.test.ts` — Unit tests for the hook\n- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/QuickFireButtons.test.tsx` — Component tests for quick-fire buttons\n- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx` — Component tests for custom event form\n- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/SeedDataButton.test.tsx` — Component tests for seed data button\n- MODIFY `src/app/test/page.tsx` — Replace stub with two-panel layout composing left panel components (right panel placeholder for future F28)\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/components/test/useEventSender.ts`** — Custom hook that:\n   - Tracks `lastDeviceId` in state (for Anonymous Page View → Button Click → Identify flow)\n   - Exposes `sendEvent(payload)` that POSTs to `/api/events` and returns success/error\n   - Exposes `sendSeed()` that POSTs to `/api/seed` then GETs `/api/seed/status`\n   - Manages per-button toast/feedback state (success message, error message, loading)\n   - Generates random device_id and user_id values for quick-fire buttons\n\n2. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/useEventSender.test.ts`** — Unit tests for the hook\n\n3. **Create `src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx`** — Renders the 5 quick-fire buttons (Anonymous Page View, Button Click, Identify User, Purchase, Signup). Each button calls `sendEvent` from the hook with the correct payload. Shows inline success/error feedback after each send.\n\n4. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/QuickFireButtons.test.tsx`** — Component tests\n\n5. **Create `src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx`** — Collapsible form with event_name, device_id, user_id, timestamp, and properties (textarea) fields. Submit button calls `sendEvent`. Shows inline success/error feedback.\n\n6. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx`** — Component tests\n\n7. **Create `src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx`** — Button that calls `POST /api/seed`, shows loading spinner, then displays event count from seed result or `/api/seed/status`.\n\n8. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/SeedDataButton.test.tsx`** — Component tests\n\n9. **Modify `src/app/test/page.tsx`** — Replace stub with two-panel layout. Left panel renders QuickFireButtons, CustomEventForm, and SeedDataButton. Right panel renders a placeholder (e.g., `<Typography>Live Feed coming soon</Typography>`) for the future live feed feature.\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] Type check: `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Lint: `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Build: `pnpm build` exits 0\n- [ ] Test suite: `pnpm test` exits with 0 failures\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/useEventSender.ts` exists and exports `useEventSender`\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx` exists and exports `QuickFireButtons`\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx` exists and exports `CustomEventForm`\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx` exists and exports `SeedDataButton`\n- [ ] File `src/app/test/page.tsx` exists and imports from `@/components/test/QuickFireButtons`\n- [ ] File `src/app/test/page.tsx` imports from `@/components/test/CustomEventForm`\n- [ ] File `src/app/test/page.tsx` imports from `@/components/test/SeedDataButton`\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `data-testid=\"quick-fire-buttons\"`\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `data-testid=\"custom-event-form\"`\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `data-testid=\"seed-data-button\"`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/useEventSender.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `useEventSender` hook from `@/components/test/useEventSender`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - `sendEvent` calls `fetch` with `POST /api/events` and correct JSON body\n  - `sendEvent` returns success state on 201 response\n  - `sendEvent` returns error message on 400/409/500 responses\n  - `lastDeviceId` is updated after sending an Anonymous Page View event\n  - `sendSeed` calls `POST /api/seed` and returns event count on success\n  - `sendSeed` returns error message on failure\n  - Loading state is true during in-flight requests, false after completion\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/QuickFireButtons.test.tsx`\n- **Module under test**: `QuickFireButtons` component from `@/components/test/QuickFireButtons`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Renders `data-testid=\"quick-fire-buttons\"` container\n  - Renders all 5 quick-fire buttons (Anonymous Page View, Button Click, Identify User, Purchase, Signup)\n  - Clicking \"Anonymous Page View\" calls `sendEvent` with `event_name: \"Page Viewed\"`, a device_id, and `{ page: \"/home\" }` properties\n  - Clicking \"Button Click\" calls `sendEvent` with `event_name: \"Button Clicked\"` and same device_id as last anonymous event\n  - Clicking \"Identify User\" calls `sendEvent` with both device_id and user_id\n  - Clicking \"Purchase\" calls `sendEvent` with user_id and `{ amount: 49.99, currency: \"USD\" }`\n  - Clicking \"Signup\" calls `sendEvent` with new random device_id and user_id\n  - Success/error feedback is displayed after a send completes\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx`\n- **Module under test**: `CustomEventForm` component from `@/components/test/CustomEventForm`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Renders `data-testid=\"custom-event-form\"` container\n  - Form is collapsible (toggle open/closed)\n  - Submit button is disabled when `event_name` is empty\n  - Submitting with valid event_name calls `sendEvent` with correct payload\n  - Optional fields (device_id, user_id, timestamp, properties) are included in payload when filled\n  - Invalid JSON in properties textarea shows validation error\n  - Success/error feedback is displayed after submit\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/SeedDataButton.test.tsx`\n- **Module under test**: `SeedDataButton` component from `@/components/test/SeedDataButton`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Renders `data-testid=\"seed-data-button\"` container\n  - Clicking the button calls `POST /api/seed`\n  - Shows loading indicator while seed is in progress\n  - Displays event count on successful completion\n  - Shows error message on failure\n\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `/test` page rendering — requires dev server\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\n1. **device_id persistence across quick-fire buttons**: The spec says \"Button Click\" uses \"same device_id as last anonymous\" and \"Identify User\" uses \"same device_id\". The `useEventSender` hook must track the last generated device_id in React state. If the user refreshes the page, this tracking resets — acceptable since this is a developer testing tool.\n2. **Properties textarea vs CodeMirror**: The spec mentions \"syntax highlighting (CodeMirror or simple `<textarea>`)\". Using a plain `<textarea>` with monospace font to avoid adding a CodeMirror dependency. The spec explicitly permits this.\n3. **Right panel placeholder**: This feature only builds the left panel. The right panel (Live Feed) will be built in a subsequent feature. A placeholder is rendered to maintain the two-panel layout structure.\n","numLines":156,"startLine":1,"totalLines":156}}}
